# The `WebAssemblyFunctionInfo` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

This class is derived from <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/machinefunctioninfo">MachineFunctionInfo</a> and contains private WebAssembly-specific information for each <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinefunction">MachineFunction</a>. <a href="#details">More...</a>

This requires remapping <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinebasicblock">MachineBasicBlock</a> references from the original parent to values in the new function. Targets may assume that virtual register and frame index values are preserved in the new function.

### VRegStackified {#a28c53b9ff6a170936977ed56fd4cd27d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="BitVector llvm::WebAssemblyFunctionInfo::VRegStackified">
A mapping from CodeGen vreg index to a boolean value indicating whether the given register is considered to be &quot;stackified&quot;, meaning it has been determined or made to meet the stack requirements:

<ul>
<li>single use (per path)</li>
<li>single def (per path)</li>
<li>defined and used in LIFO order with other stack registers</li>
</ul>

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/webassembly/webassemblymachinefunctioninfo-h/#l00048">48</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/webassembly/webassemblymachinefunctioninfo-h">WebAssemblyMachineFunctionInfo.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
